{"parentUuid":"450ff1a6-47f3-4dbf-94ee-df5bdaa905c1","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/aharbuz/code/aharbuz/claude-playground/pocket-gris","sessionId":"f548b4b2-f4bf-4534-a1ab-8d9289d818ea","version":"2.1.34","gitBranch":"main","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YB3RBC5Taja5BBRpYq4sXA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on what I know (up to May 2025), Apple Intelligence doesn't have a dedicated video background removal feature. Here's what exists in the Apple ecosystem:\n\n**What Apple offers:**\n- **Photos app** can lift subjects from **still images** (iOS 16+/macOS Ventura+) — tap and hold a subject to separate it from the background\n- **iOS 17+** extended this to lift subjects from **paused video frames**, but it produces a still image, not a processed video\n- **FaceTime** has a \"Portrait\" mode that blurs backgrounds in real-time, but that's only for video calls\n\n**What it doesn't do:**\n- There's no built-in tool to remove/replace backgrounds from recorded video clips across the OS\n\n**Better alternatives for video background removal:**\n- **Final Cut Pro** — has background removal/chroma key tools\n- **DaVinci Resolve** (free) — solid keying and masking\n- **RunwayML** — AI-powered video background removal in the browser\n- **CapCut** — has auto background removal for video on mobile\n\nWant me to look up whether anything new has shipped since mid-2025?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":18397,"cache_read_input_tokens":16171,"output_tokens":319,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":18397,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0}}},"requestId":"req_011CXrtLcL2voce81CZfNDiQ","type":"assistant","uuid":"ae31105f-8142-4820-b215-25486b3a3a7f","timestamp":"2026-02-06T13:22:14.190Z"}
